description: Despite global criticism, Sweden has seen a drop in serious Covid cases without ever having a lockdown.
title: Did Sweden's coronavirus strategy succeed or fail?
title_page: Did Sweden's coronavirus strategy succeed or fail? - BBC News
maintext: "It feels good. I mean, finally, we are where we hoped we would be much earlier on," says Anders Tegnell, the state epidemiologist leading the strategy. He's admitted too many have died, especially in Swedish care homes. But he believes there is still "no strong evidence that a lockdown would have made that much of a difference".
